user_request: A poem about a road not taken and the difference it made.
final_poem:
Two paths diverged in morning's hush
The one I took, a winding rush
Through familiar hills and verdant space
 Led me to where I now pace

But on that dawn, another road did lie
A route less traveled, whispered by the sky
It beckoned with a siren's call
To leave the known and take it all

If I had taken that unseen way
Would I have found a brighter day?
Perhaps in distant fields I'd roam
Free from the choices made back home

Or maybe not. Maybe I would've strayed
Into darker woods, lost in dismay
The road not taken, an unknown fate
A mystery we can never participate
